  "text": "Our patient population also differs significantly from that of Stevens et al. [CITATION_1] . Nineteen of their 24 patients had a generalised skeletal dysplasia. We excluded such patients from our series as our interest was in the aetiology of isolated os odontoideum. Those with an associated skeletal dysplasia are likely to have a congenital aetiology and often have additional factors such as ligamentous laxity contributing to the pathology.",
